ANDREw de Moravia succeeded in 1222, ² but was not consecrated till after 1223. He was probably the son of Hugh de Moravia, Lord of Duffus, and, before being raised to the Bishoprick, Parson of Duffus, in which character he consented to the erection of the chapel. ² In his time—in 1224—the transference of the Episcopal See and the Cathedral of the Diocese to Elgin was effected, which had probably been designed and solicited by his predecessor.
